{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "StagePrognosis",
        "description": "Stochastic individual-tree growth model for lodgepole pine (Pinus contorta) based on the Prognosis Model for Stand Development (Stage 1973). Tracks squared diameter (Dsq = DBH²), total height (HT), height to crown base (HCB), and tree density (N_trees) under four coupled processes: basal area increment (Stage 1973 Eq. 1), height growth (Eq. 2), crown recession (Eq. 3), and endemic mortality (Eq. 4). The upstream Julia source includes a multiplicative Brownian noise term on DDS_rate (gt-kuxo gap); this ESM migrates the deterministic drift equations only. All quantities in SI base units (m, s); upstream regression fitted in imperial units (inches, feet, years) — parameters encode the conversion constants. Migrated from Vegetation.jl@010c3774dc5646d81806c6119c8a029a70f6c9a0:src/stage_prognosis.jl:29.",
        "tags": [
            "vegetation",
            "forest_growth",
            "individual_tree",
            "stochastic",
            "sde",
            "stage1973",
            "lodgepole_pine"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-21T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "Vegetation.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-ookb)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Stage, A.R. (1973). Prognosis model for stand development. USDA Forest Service Research Paper INT-137. Intermountain Forest and Range Experiment Station, Ogden, Utah. 32 p."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "StagePrognosis": {
            "reference": {
                "citation": "Stage, A.R. (1973). Prognosis model for stand development. USDA Forest Service Research Paper INT-137.",
                "notes": "source_ref: Vegetation.jl@010c3774dc5646d81806c6119c8a029a70f6c9a0:src/stage_prognosis.jl:29\n\nUpstream StagePrognosis is an MTK @component implementing Stage (1973). It declares 4 ODE state @variables (Dsq, HT, HCB, N_trees), 8 algebraic @variables (DBH, CR, DDS_rate, DG, HTGF_rate, crown_recession_rate, mortality_rate, mean_DBH_in), 1 @brownians B_growth (Wiener noise for stochastic diameter growth), and two @constants blocks plus one @parameters block. The presence of B_growth promotes the MTK system to an SDESystem.\n\nUpstream @constants are preserved as parameters with their fixed defaults — same pattern as components/vegetation/landis_biomass.esm — so the standalone ESM model is fully self-contained. The parameter sigma_growth corresponds to Julia's σ_growth = 0.3 * sqrt(3.15576e7) ≈ 1685.28 (dimensionless); setting it to 0 recovers the deterministic limit used in the inline tests.\n\nKey equations (Stage 1973 equation numbering):\n  Eq. 1: DDS_rate = BKR * (in²/yr) * exp(b0 + b1*ln(SI_ft) + b2*EL_hft + b3*ln(CCF) + b4*ln(CR) + b5*ln(DBH_in) + b6*PCT)  [diameter squared growth rate, converted to m²/s]\n  Eq. 2: HTGF_rate = (ft/yr) * exp(c1 + c2*ln(DG+0.05) + c3*ln(DBH_in) + c4*ln(HT_ft))  [height growth rate, m/s]\n  Eq. 3: crown_recession_rate = (0.20 or 0.61)*HTGF_rate  [CCF threshold at 125]\n  Eq. 4: mortality_rate = (1/yr) * (a0 + a1*DBH_mean_in + a2*DBH_mean_in²) * (0.25 + 1.5*(1 - PCT/100))  [Lee 1971]\n  SDE: D(Dsq) = DDS_rate + sigma_growth * |DDS_rate| * B_growth  [multiplicative noise]\n\nTolerance rationale (rel=1e-4): all RHS terms involve smooth transcendental functions of bounded state variables; with sigma_growth=0 the system is a well-posed ODE. The nested exp/log structure produces moderate condition numbers — rel=1e-4 gives comfortable margin above integration error while staying well within the physical uncertainty of Stage's empirical regression (~10-15% RMS residual in log-space).\n\nTODO_GAP: gt-kuxo — Upstream Julia component uses `@brownians B_growth` to add multiplicative Wiener noise to the diameter growth equation:\n  D(Dsq) ~ DDS_rate + sigma_growth * abs(DDS_rate) * B_growth\nThe ESM schema v0.4.0 has no `brownian` variable type (gap gt-kuxo). This ESM migrates the deterministic drift only: D(Dsq) = DDS_rate. sigma_growth is preserved as a structural parameter (default=0.0 for deterministic operation). When gt-kuxo is resolved, add `B_growth` as a `type: brownian` variable and restore the full SDE equation."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 0.0001
            },
            "variables": {
                "one_inch": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 0.0254,
                    "description": "Reference length: 1 inch in meters. Converts SI lengths to the inches used in Stage (1973) regression coefficients."
                },
                "one_foot": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 0.3048,
                    "description": "Reference length: 1 foot in meters. Converts SI lengths to the feet used in Stage (1973) site index and height regressions."
                },
                "hundred_feet": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 30.48,
                    "description": "Reference length: 100 feet in meters. Converts elevation to the hundreds-of-feet units in the DDS regression."
                },
                "one_inch_sq": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^2",
                    "default": 0.00064516,
                    "description": "Reference area: 1 square inch in m². Converts DDS from in²/yr to m²/yr in the basal area increment equation."
                },
                "one_year": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "s",
                    "default": 31557600.0,
                    "description": "Reference time: 1 year in seconds (365.25 days). Converts annual rates to per-second rates throughout."
                },
                "b_DDS_0": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": -1.66955,
                    "description": "DDS regression intercept (Stage 1973, p. 15, dimensionless)."
                },
                "b_DDS_SI": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.4143,
                    "description": "DDS coefficient on ln(SI in feet) (Stage 1973, p. 15, dimensionless)."
                },
                "b_DDS_EL": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": -0.004388,
                    "description": "DDS coefficient on elevation in hundreds of feet (Stage 1973, p. 15, dimensionless)."
                },
                "b_DDS_CCF": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": -0.3781,
                    "description": "DDS coefficient on ln(CCF) (Stage 1973, p. 15, dimensionless). Negative: higher competition reduces growth."
                },
                "b_DDS_CR": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.4879,
                    "description": "DDS coefficient on ln(crown ratio CR) (Stage 1973, p. 15, dimensionless)."
                },
                "b_DDS_DBH": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.9948,
                    "description": "DDS coefficient on ln(DBH in inches) (Stage 1973, p. 15, dimensionless). Near 1.0: growth scales roughly linearly with DBH."
                },
                "b_DDS_PCT": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.006141,
                    "description": "DDS coefficient on percentile PCT (Stage 1973, p. 15, dimensionless). Positive: dominant trees grow faster."
                },
                "crown_recess_low": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.2,
                    "description": "Crown recession fraction when CCF < 125: crown base rises at 1/5 of height growth rate (Stage 1973, p. 16)."
                },
                "crown_recess_high": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.61,
                    "description": "Crown recession fraction when CCF >= 125: crown base rises at 0.61 of height growth rate (Stage 1973, p. 16)."
                },
                "CCF_threshold": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 125.0,
                    "description": "Crown competition factor threshold separating low and high crown recession regimes (Stage 1973, p. 16)."
                },
                "mort_a0": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.0536,
                    "description": "Mortality intercept (Lee 1971 via Stage 1973, p. 16-17). Annual rate at mean DBH = 0, dimensionless."
                },
                "mort_a1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": -0.0088,
                    "description": "Mortality linear coefficient on mean DBH in inches (Lee 1971 via Stage 1973, p. 16-17). Negative: larger stands have lower base mortality."
                },
                "mort_a2": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.000415,
                    "description": "Mortality quadratic coefficient on mean DBH² in inches² (Lee 1971 via Stage 1973, p. 16-17). Minimum at DBH ≈ 10.6 inches."
                },
                "CR_min": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.01,
                    "description": "Minimum crown ratio floor to prevent log(0) in DDS regression (dimensionless)."
                },
                "DG_min": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.001,
                    "description": "Minimum diameter growth increment floor in inches-space to prevent log(0) in height growth regression (dimensionless)."
                },
                "DG_offset": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.05,
                    "description": "Offset added to DG before log transform in height growth regression: ln(DG + 0.05) (Stage 1973, p. 15-16)."
                },
                "zero_rate": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1/s",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Zero rate used as floor in max() for mortality (prevents negative mortality rates)."
                },
                "one_rate_per_year": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1/s",
                    "default": 3.170979198376459e-08,
                    "description": "Unit annual rate converted to per-second: 1 / 3.15576e7. Converts annual mortality coefficients to SI units."
                },
                "mort_base_factor": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.25,
                    "description": "Base mortality distribution factor for dominant trees (PCT=100): mortality = base_rate * 0.25 (Stage 1973, p. 17)."
                },
                "mort_scale_factor": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 1.5,
                    "description": "Mortality distribution scale: factor = 0.25 + 1.5*(1 - PCT/100), ranging from 0.25 (dominant) to 1.75 (suppressed, Stage 1973, p. 17)."
                },
                "mort_pct_one": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Unity constant for PCT normalization in mortality distribution factor: (1 - PCT/100)."
                },
                "mort_pct_max": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 100.0,
                    "description": "Maximum percentile value for PCT normalization in mortality distribution factor."
                },
                "SI": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 24.384,
                    "description": "Site index: dominant stand height at base age, in meters. Default 80 ft = 80 * 0.3048 m (Stage 1973 example, p. 5)."
                },
                "EL": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 1310.64,
                    "description": "Elevation above sea level in meters. Default 4300 ft = 43 * 30.48 m (Stage 1973 example, p. 5)."
                },
                "CCF": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 100.0,
                    "description": "Crown competition factor: dimensionless index of stand density (Krajicek 1961). Default 100 corresponds to fully-stocked stand."
                },
                "PCT": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 50.0,
                    "description": "Percentile of tree in basal area distribution (0 = smallest, 100 = largest). Affects both growth (DDS) and mortality."
                },
                "RMSQD": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 0.1778,
                    "description": "Diameter of the tree of mean basal area in the stand, in meters. Default 7 in = 7 * 0.0254 m."
                },
                "BKR": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Bark ratio (dob/dib)²: ratio of outside-bark to inside-bark diameter squared. Default 1.0 neglects bark thickness."
                },
                "c1_ht": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Height increment intercept coefficient (Cole & Stage, in preparation, referenced in Stage 1973, p. 15-16). Dimensionless."
                },
                "c2_ht": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.5,
                    "description": "Height increment coefficient on ln(DG + 0.05) (Cole & Stage, in preparation). Dimensionless."
                },
                "c3_ht": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": -0.1,
                    "description": "Height increment coefficient on ln(DBH in inches) (Cole & Stage, in preparation). Negative: taller/larger trees grow proportionally less in height."
                },
                "c4_ht": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.2,
                    "description": "Height increment coefficient on ln(HT in feet) (Cole & Stage, in preparation). Positive: taller trees grow more in height."
                },
                "mean_DBH": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 0.1778,
                    "description": "Stand mean DBH for mortality calculation in meters. Default 7 in = 7 * 0.0254 m. Matches RMSQD default."
                },
                "sigma_growth": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Scaled standard deviation of stochastic growth noise: 0.3 * sqrt(one_year) = 0.3 * sqrt(3.15576e7) ≈ 1685.28 in the upstream Julia SDE. Retained as a structural parameter but not used in the deterministic equation (see TODO_GAP: gt-kuxo). Default is 0.0 (deterministic limit)."
                },
                "Dsq": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m^2",
                    "default": 0.02322576,
                    "description": "Squared diameter at breast height (DBH²) in m². Carried as state variable because basal area increment is most naturally linear in diameter-squared space. Default: (6 in)² = (6 * 0.0254 m)² = 0.02322576 m²."
                },
                "HT": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 18.288,
                    "description": "Total tree height in meters. Default 60 ft = 60 * 0.3048 = 18.288 m (Stage 1973 example, p. 5)."
                },
                "HCB": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 12.192,
                    "description": "Height to crown base in meters. Default 40 ft = 40 * 0.3048 = 12.192 m, giving initial crown ratio CR = 1/3."
                },
                "N_trees": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m^-2",
                    "default": 0.12355445,
                    "description": "Tree density in trees per m². Default 500 trees/acre = 500 / 4046.86 ≈ 0.12355 m^-2 (Stage 1973 example, p. 5)."
                },
                "DBH": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m",
                    "description": "Diameter at breast height in meters. Algebraic: DBH = sqrt(Dsq)."
                },
                "CR": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Crown ratio (live crown length / total height). Algebraic: CR = max(CR_min, (HT - HCB) / HT). Bounded below by CR_min to prevent log(0) in DDS regression."
                },
                "DDS_rate": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m^2/s",
                    "description": "Rate of change of squared diameter (basal area increment rate) in m²/s. Algebraic: BKR * (1 in²/yr) * exp(Stage 1973 Eq. 1 regression). Drift term in the D(Dsq) SDE."
                },
                "DG": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Periodic diameter increment in inches-space (dimensionless ratio: new_DBH_in - old_DBH_in). Derived from DDS_rate * one_year to connect the annual DDS to the height-growth regression (Stage 1973, p. 15-16). Floored at DG_min."
                },
                "HTGF_rate": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "description": "Height growth rate in m/s. Algebraic: (1 ft/yr) * exp(Cole & Stage regression on DG, DBH_in, HT_ft). Drift term in D(HT)."
                },
                "crown_recession_rate": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "description": "Rate of crown base rise in m/s. Algebraic: fraction * HTGF_rate, where fraction = 0.20 if CCF < 125 (open-stand regime) or 0.61 if CCF >= 125 (dense-stand regime) (Stage 1973, p. 16). Drift term in D(HCB)."
                },
                "mortality_rate": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1/s",
                    "description": "Per-capita mortality rate in s^-1. Algebraic: (1/yr) * Lee(mean_DBH_in) * percentile_factor(PCT), floored at zero (Stage 1973, Eq. 4 from Lee 1971)."
                },
                "mean_DBH_in": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Stand mean DBH in inches (dimensionless): mean_DBH / one_inch. Used in the Lee (1971) mortality regression."
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "lhs": "DBH",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "sqrt",
                        "args": [
                            "Dsq"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "CR",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "max",
                        "args": [
                            "CR_min",
                            {
                                "op": "/",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "+",
                                        "args": [
                                            "HT",
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    -1,
                                                    "HCB"
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    "HT"
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "mean_DBH_in",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            "mean_DBH",
                            "one_inch"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "DDS_rate",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "/",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            "BKR",
                                            "one_inch_sq"
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    "one_year"
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "exp",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "+",
                                        "args": [
                                            "b_DDS_0",
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "b_DDS_SI",
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "log",
                                                        "args": [
                                                            {
                                                                "op": "/",
                                                                "args": [
                                                                    "SI",
                                                                    "one_foot"
                                                                ]
                                                            }
                                                        ]
                                                    }
                                                ]
                                            },
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "b_DDS_EL",
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "/",
                                                        "args": [
                                                            "EL",
                                                            "hundred_feet"
                                                        ]
                                                    }
                                                ]
                                            },
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "b_DDS_CCF",
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "log",
                                                        "args": [
                                                            "CCF"
                                                        ]
                                                    }
                                                ]
                                            },
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "b_DDS_CR",
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "log",
                                                        "args": [
                                                            "CR"
                                                        ]
                                                    }
                                                ]
                                            },
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "b_DDS_DBH",
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "log",
                                                        "args": [
                                                            {
                                                                "op": "/",
                                                                "args": [
                                                                    "DBH",
                                                                    "one_inch"
                                                                ]
                                                            }
                                                        ]
                                                    }
                                                ]
                                            },
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "b_DDS_PCT",
                                                    "PCT"
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "DG",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "max",
                        "args": [
                            "DG_min",
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "sqrt",
                                        "args": [
                                            {
                                                "op": "+",
                                                "args": [
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "^",
                                                        "args": [
                                                            {
                                                                "op": "/",
                                                                "args": [
                                                                    "DBH",
                                                                    "one_inch"
                                                                ]
                                                            },
                                                            2
                                                        ]
                                                    },
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "/",
                                                        "args": [
                                                            {
                                                                "op": "*",
                                                                "args": [
                                                                    "DDS_rate",
                                                                    "one_year"
                                                                ]
                                                            },
                                                            "one_inch_sq"
                                                        ]
                                                    }
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            -1,
                                            {
                                                "op": "/",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "DBH",
                                                    "one_inch"
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "HTGF_rate",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "/",
                                "args": [
                                    "one_foot",
                                    "one_year"
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "exp",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "+",
                                        "args": [
                                            "c1_ht",
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "c2_ht",
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "log",
                                                        "args": [
                                                            {
                                                                "op": "+",
                                                                "args": [
                                                                    "DG",
                                                                    "DG_offset"
                                                                ]
                                                            }
                                                        ]
                                                    }
                                                ]
                                            },
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "c3_ht",
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "log",
                                                        "args": [
                                                            {
                                                                "op": "/",
                                                                "args": [
                                                                    "DBH",
                                                                    "one_inch"
                                                                ]
                                                            }
                                                        ]
                                                    }
                                                ]
                                            },
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "c4_ht",
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "log",
                                                        "args": [
                                                            {
                                                                "op": "/",
                                                                "args": [
                                                                    "HT",
                                                                    "one_foot"
                                                                ]
                                                            }
                                                        ]
                                                    }
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "crown_recession_rate",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "ifelse",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "<",
                                "args": [
                                    "CCF",
                                    "CCF_threshold"
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    "crown_recess_low",
                                    "HTGF_rate"
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    "crown_recess_high",
                                    "HTGF_rate"
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "mortality_rate",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "max",
                        "args": [
                            "zero_rate",
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    "one_rate_per_year",
                                    {
                                        "op": "+",
                                        "args": [
                                            "mort_a0",
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "mort_a1",
                                                    "mean_DBH_in"
                                                ]
                                            },
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "mort_a2",
                                                    "mean_DBH_in",
                                                    "mean_DBH_in"
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "+",
                                        "args": [
                                            "mort_base_factor",
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "mort_scale_factor",
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "+",
                                                        "args": [
                                                            "mort_pct_one",
                                                            {
                                                                "op": "*",
                                                                "args": [
                                                                    -1,
                                                                    {
                                                                        "op": "/",
                                                                        "args": [
                                                                            "PCT",
                                                                            "mort_pct_max"
                                                                        ]
                                                                    }
                                                                ]
                                                            }
                                                        ]
                                                    }
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": {
                        "op": "D",
                        "wrt": "t",
                        "args": [
                            "Dsq"
                        ]
                    },
                    "rhs": "DDS_rate"
                },
                {
                    "lhs": {
                        "op": "D",
                        "wrt": "t",
                        "args": [
                            "HT"
                        ]
                    },
                    "rhs": "HTGF_rate"
                },
                {
                    "lhs": {
                        "op": "D",
                        "wrt": "t",
                        "args": [
                            "HCB"
                        ]
                    },
                    "rhs": "crown_recession_rate"
                },
                {
                    "lhs": {
                        "op": "D",
                        "wrt": "t",
                        "args": [
                            "N_trees"
                        ]
                    },
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            -1,
                            "mortality_rate",
                            "N_trees"
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "t0-algebraic-identity",
                    "description": "At t=0 with default ICs, DBH = sqrt(Dsq), CR = (HT-HCB)/HT = 1/3 exactly, mean_DBH_in = mean_DBH/one_inch = 7.0 exactly.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "sigma_growth": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "DBH",
                            "time": 0,
                            "expected": 0.1524,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "abs": 1e-10
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "CR",
                            "time": 0,
                            "expected": 0.33333333333,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 1e-06
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "mean_DBH_in",
                            "time": 0,
                            "expected": 7.0,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "abs": 1e-10
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "t0-growth-and-mortality-rates",
                    "description": "At t=0 with defaults (sigma_growth=0), verify computed algebraic rates: DDS_rate from Stage (1973) Eq. 1, DG derived from DDS_rate, HTGF_rate from height regression, mortality_rate from Lee (1971). Values computed from the closed-form regression with DBH=6in, HT=60ft, CR=1/3, CCF=100, SI=80ft, EL=43 hft, PCT=50.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "sigma_growth": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "DDS_rate",
                            "time": 0,
                            "expected": 1.623e-11,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.03
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "DG",
                            "time": 0,
                            "expected": 0.0658,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.03
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "HTGF_rate",
                            "time": 0,
                            "expected": 6.23e-09,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.03
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "mortality_rate",
                            "time": 0,
                            "expected": 3.909e-10,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.03
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "t0-crown-recession-low-ccf",
                    "description": "At t=0 with CCF=100 < CCF_threshold=125, crown recession uses the low factor (0.20 * HTGF_rate).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "sigma_growth": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "crown_recession_rate",
                            "time": 0,
                            "expected": 1.246e-09,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.03
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "t0-crown-recession-high-ccf",
                    "description": "At t=0 with CCF=200 >= CCF_threshold=125, crown recession switches to the high factor (0.61 * HTGF_rate). Tests the ifelse branch in the crown_recession_rate equation.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "sigma_growth": 0.0,
                        "CCF": 200.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "crown_recession_rate",
                            "time": 0,
                            "expected": 3.548e-09,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.05
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "height-diameter-growth-11yr",
                    "description": "Deterministic 11-year projection (sigma_growth=0) from default ICs. Validates diameter and height growth magnitude against Stage (1973) Figure 1B trajectory (~0.65 ft/yr height growth, ~0.09 in/yr diameter growth). Crown base rises with tree. Tree density decreases due to endemic mortality.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "sigma_growth": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 347133600
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "HT",
                            "time": 347133600,
                            "expected": 20.45,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.05
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "Dsq",
                            "time": 347133600,
                            "expected": 0.02886,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.06
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "DBH",
                            "time": 347133600,
                            "expected": 0.1699,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.04
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "HCB",
                            "time": 347133600,
                            "expected": 12.625,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.05
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "N_trees",
                            "time": 347133600,
                            "expected": 0.10788,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.06
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "long-run-50yr",
                    "description": "Deterministic 50-year projection (sigma_growth=0) from default ICs. Verifies sustained growth and mortality over a realistic stand development period.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "sigma_growth": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 1577880000
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "HT",
                            "time": 1577880000,
                            "expected": 27.0,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.15
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "N_trees",
                            "time": 1577880000,
                            "expected": 0.0667,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.12
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "Dsq",
                            "time": 1577880000,
                            "expected": 0.0611,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.1
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "HCB",
                            "time": 1577880000,
                            "expected": 14.16,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.12
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "site-index-low",
                    "description": "Low site index (SI=50 ft = 15.24 m): DDS_rate scales as SI^b_DDS_SI. At SI=50ft vs default SI=80ft, ratio = (50/80)^0.4143 ≈ 0.823, so DDS_rate ≈ 0.823 * baseline.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "sigma_growth": 0.0,
                        "SI": 15.24
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "DDS_rate",
                            "time": 0,
                            "expected": 1.336e-11,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.03
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "site-index-high",
                    "description": "High site index (SI=100 ft = 30.48 m): DDS_rate scales as SI^b_DDS_SI. At SI=100ft vs default SI=80ft, ratio = (100/80)^0.4143 ≈ 1.097, so DDS_rate ≈ 1.097 * baseline.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "sigma_growth": 0.0,
                        "SI": 30.48
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "DDS_rate",
                            "time": 0,
                            "expected": 1.78e-11,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.03
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "ccf-low-competition",
                    "description": "Low competition (CCF=50): less crowding increases basal area growth (DDS_rate ~ CCF^b_DDS_CCF, ratio vs CCF=100 is (50/100)^(-0.3781) ≈ 1.299). Also tests height growth rate which is higher due to larger DG.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "sigma_growth": 0.0,
                        "CCF": 50.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "DDS_rate",
                            "time": 0,
                            "expected": 2.109e-11,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.03
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "HTGF_rate",
                            "time": 0,
                            "expected": 6.74e-09,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.04
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "ccf-high-competition",
                    "description": "High competition (CCF=200): dense crowding reduces growth (DDS_rate ~ CCF^b_DDS_CCF, ratio vs CCF=100 is (200/100)^(-0.3781) ≈ 0.770). CCF=200 also exceeds CCF_threshold=125 so crown_recession_rate uses the 0.61 multiplier.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "sigma_growth": 0.0,
                        "CCF": 200.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "DDS_rate",
                            "time": 0,
                            "expected": 1.249e-11,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.03
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "HTGF_rate",
                            "time": 0,
                            "expected": 5.817e-09,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.05
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "mortality-pct-dominant",
                    "description": "High PCT=90 (dominant tree): mortality distribution factor = 0.25 + 1.5*(1-0.9) = 0.40, giving lower per-capita mortality than PCT=50 (factor=1.0). Tests Stage (1973) p. 17 size-stratified mortality.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "sigma_growth": 0.0,
                        "PCT": 90.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "mortality_rate",
                            "time": 0,
                            "expected": 1.563e-10,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.03
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "mortality-pct-suppressed",
                    "description": "Low PCT=10 (suppressed tree): mortality distribution factor = 0.25 + 1.5*(1-0.1) = 1.60, giving higher per-capita mortality than PCT=50 (factor=1.0). Tests Stage (1973) p. 17 size-stratified mortality.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "sigma_growth": 0.0,
                        "PCT": 10.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "mortality_rate",
                            "time": 0,
                            "expected": 6.254e-10,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 0.03
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "50yr_deterministic_growth",
                    "description": "Deterministic 50-year stand development trajectory (sigma_growth=0) from default initial conditions: 6-inch DBH, 60-foot tall lodgepole pine at site index 80 ft, elevation 43 hundreds-of-feet, CCF=100. Shows coupled growth of Dsq and HT with concurrent crown recession and endemic mortality thinning the stand.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 1577880000
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "height_diameter_growth",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Tree height (HT) and DBH over 50 years of deterministic growth.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "t",
                                "label": "time (s)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "HT",
                                "label": "HT (m)"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "stand_density",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Tree density (N_trees) decline over 50 years due to endemic mortality.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "t",
                                "label": "time (s)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "N_trees",
                                "label": "N_trees (m-2)"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "site_index_comparison",
                    "description": "Compare growth trajectories across three site indices: SI=50 ft (15.24 m, poor site), SI=80 ft (24.384 m, default), and SI=100 ft (30.48 m, good site). Higher site index produces faster diameter and height growth as modeled by Stage (1973) Eq. 1. All runs are deterministic (sigma_growth=0).",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 1262304000
                    },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "SI",
                                "values": [
                                    15.24,
                                    24.384,
                                    30.48
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "dsq_by_site_index",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Squared DBH (Dsq) over 40 years for three site indices. Higher SI accelerates basal area growth.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "t",
                                "label": "time (s)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "Dsq",
                                "label": "Dsq (m^2)"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
